First thing that came to mind for me (just assuming there was needed a practical way to do it) was the following (translated into Python):<p><pre><code>  # associative array / dict / hash
  store = {}
  for elem in inputlist:
    if elem in store:
      del store[elem]
    else:
      store[elem] = True
  # return the only key left
  return store.keys()[0]
